Manufacturing Product Manual

Battery Issues
--------------
Overheating can occur due to firmware bugs or damaged battery cells.

Battery Drain
-------------
High background CPU usage after firmware updates may reduce battery life.

Display Problems
----------------
Loose display connectors may cause intermittent flickering.

Audio
-----
Damaged speaker modules should be replaced.

Camera
------
Blurred images are generally caused by faulty camera lenses.

Networking
----------
WiFi disconnections are often resolved by updating network drivers.

Packaging
----------
Weak cartons may cause transportation damage.

Motor
-----
Motor vibration usually indicates loose shaft alignment.